<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Stacked washer-dryer units in LA apartments — especially in West Hollywood, Silver Lake, Koreatown, and Mid-Wilshire — are one of the most common repair scenarios we encounter. These compact configurations in laundry closets present specific access challenges: sometimes the dryer must come off the stack to reach the washer, and working in a 24-inch closet opening requires technique, not just parts knowledge.</p>
<p>Our technicians are trained specifically on stacked configurations common in LA's apartment stock. We assess the installation before quoting — if additional access labor is needed, you see that cost upfront in the quote before we start. LA stacked units also tend to run harder than single-family home units from higher-frequency use in rental buildings, which means drain pump and door latch failures occur earlier than manufacturer failure rate estimates.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">🏠 LA apartment stackeds — what makes them different</div>
      <p>Stacked units in LA apartments have two characteristics that affect repair: first, access is tight and sometimes requires removing the dryer from the stack to service the washer. Second, high-use rental units see drain pump, door latch, and bearing failures earlier than owner-occupied units. Both factors are reflected in an honest upfront quote — transparent pricing mid-repair.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
